	<key>NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription</key>
    <string>PlantSpotify needs access to your photo library so you can select existing plant photos for instant species identification and disease diagnosis. For example, choose a photo of a plant from your camera roll to identify its species or check for pests and health issues.</string>

    <key>NSPhotoLibraryAddUsageDescription</key>
    <string>PlantSpotify saves identified plant images and diagnosis results to your photo library. For example, after identifying a plant species, you can save the result image to your camera roll to reference later or share with others.</string>
    <key>NSAppleMusicUsageDescription</key>
	<string>This app requires access to your media library to enhance your experience with audio playback and media management.</string>
	<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PlantSpotify uses your camera to photograph plants for instant species identification and disease diagnosis. For example, point your camera at a houseplant to identify its species, or capture a leaf showing yellow spots to diagnose a potential pest or nutrient deficiency.</string>
	<key>NSFileSystemUsageDescription</key>
	<string>We need access to your files for document management.</string>
